ent the first indications of correlated radio and\nX-ray variability on minute timescales in quiescence, tentatively measuring the\nradio emission to lag the X-ray by 15+/-4 min, suggestive of X-ray variations\npropagating down a jet of length <3.0 AU.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 9 Nov 2016 04:09:09 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-01-11"}
